  "name": "Morrison COU2 — Non-cannulated F1717 Compression-Bending MRL-5 Credibility Assessment (NC-3 Clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct at Model Risk Level 5. COU2 extends the Nagaraja COU1 validation envelope to a Morrison-archetype design variant with independent mesh, independent material characterisation, and independent laboratory verification. All 13 ASME V&V 40 factors assessed at high rigor (requiredLevel 4–5, achievedLevel meeting or exceeding requirement). Full UQ propagation via Monte Carlo (N=10 000) and global sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) are linked. Decision: Accepted on the basis that all 13 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels and all QoI comparisons satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds.",
